# Wholesale Invoicing Process

## Overview

Invoicing is the process of generating and transmitting billing records for shipped wholesale orders. Accurate invoicing ensures that organizations receive timely payment while maintaining financial transparency with retail partners.

Invoices are typically generated once orders have shipped and shipment confirmation has been recorded.

---

## Invoice Generation

Invoices are usually created automatically through enterprise systems such as:

• ERP platforms  
• EDI integration platforms  
• retailer vendor portals  

Automated invoice generation reduces manual errors and improves billing efficiency.

---

## Invoice Data Elements

A typical wholesale invoice contains the following information:

• invoice number  
• purchase order number  
• SKU or product identifier  
• shipped quantities  
• pricing and discounts  
• shipment date  
• payment terms  

Accurate invoice data is essential to ensure payment processing.

---

## Invoice Transmission

Invoices may be transmitted through several channels including:

• EDI invoice transactions (EDI 810)  
• retailer portals  
• automated ERP integrations  

Transmission methods depend on retailer system requirements.

---

## Invoice Validation

Operations and finance teams may validate invoices to ensure:

• pricing matches agreed terms  
• shipped quantities are correct  
• shipment documentation is accurate  
• invoice format meets retailer requirements  

Early validation reduces disputes and delayed payments.

---

## Operational Coordination

Invoicing often requires coordination between:

• operations teams  
• finance departments  
• logistics teams  
• system integration teams  

This coordination ensures invoice data aligns with shipment records.

---

## Final Note

Accurate invoicing ensures financial integrity within wholesale operations. Reliable billing processes support strong retailer relationships and predictable cash flow.
